text:
Fortieth Ave. (formerly Payntor Ave., left foreground), at the N.W. corner of 30th Street (formerly Lockwood Street). The two frame structures at the left background, rear views, face on 29th Street, formerly 122-124 Academy Street.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

30th Street (left), at the N.E. corner of 40th Avenue, looking northeastward toward the I.R.T. elevated on 31st Street.

P. L. Sperr
September 5, 1940
